To promote international academic exchange on Zhou Enlai studies as well as the research in the relation between contemporary Chinese political figures and contemporary Chinese history, “The Fourth International Conference on Zhou Enlai Studies” will be held in Nankai University, Tianjin, China in the fall of 2013. Submission of papers from experts and scholars both at home and abroad are invited. All manner of supports for the Conference are also welcomed from those who have shown great interest in Zhou Enlai Studies.

The Conference would be another grand academic event after the success of the first three conferences of the kind. It will be co-hosted by China Institute of CPC Literature Research and Nankai University, with Zhou Enlai Life Research Association, Zhou Enlai School of Government, Marxism Educational School and Zhou Enlai Research Center of Nankai University being the organizers of the Conference.

Requirements for paper submission are as follows:

1. In the principle of academic diversity, papers for the Conference are allowed to expound upon differing opinions, with topics centering either on those suggested by the Conference or on whatever the contributors feel like.

2. Contributors must abide by academic morality and norms. Either academic views based on serious research and reliable arguments or presentation of new historical materials is favorably welcomed. Works of re-inventing wheels are rejected.

3. The language of the papers may either be Chinese, English, Japanese and Russian. Chinese scholars should provide Chinese and English abstracts as well as brief personal information (inclusive of name, nation, gender, age, nationality, work place, position/academic title, level of education, area of expertise, contact number, address, email, etc.). International scholars please follow international conventions to provide brief personal information and an abstract in English.

4. Please email your paper, author’s personal information and Chinese and English abstract at xuxing2013@sina.com. Or you may also post the printed paper to: Prof. Xu Xing, Zhou Enlai school of Government, Nankai University, Tianjin ,China ( Postal Code 300071). The deadline for paper submission is June 30, 2013.

5. All papers will be read and examined by the Organizing Team of the Conference. Notification of Invitation will be sent to authors of selected papers by the end of September, 2013.

The Organizing Team of “The Fourth International

Conference on Zhou Enlai Studies”

June 2012.

Appendix: Suggested topics for the Fourth International Conference on Zhou Enlai Studies

Theme: Zhou Enlai and China in the 20th century.

Suggested topics:

1. Zhou Enlai and economic construction and social management

2. Zhou Enlai and Chinese diplomacy and international relations

3. Zhou Enlai and Chinese political party politics and government management

4. Zhou Enlai and national solidarity and state unity

5. Zhou Enlai and science, education, culture, health and sports in China

6. Zhou Enlai and armed battle and national defense construction

7. Zhou Enlai’s individual quality

8. Latest study on Zhou Enlai’s career

9. Comparative analysis of Zhou Enlai’s thoughts

10. Analysis on Zhou Enlai's historical status, influence, and personality

